	<h2 style="margin: 0.66em 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.1em; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 1.2em;">
		Dietitian</h2>

	<p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 20px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; margin-bottom: 8px !important;">
		<strong style="margin: 0px;"><span class="baec5a81-e4d6-4674-97f3-e9220f0136c1" style="white-space: nowrap;">(940) 565-2333<a href="#" style="margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;" title="Call: (940) 565-2333"><img src="data:image/png;base64," style="margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;" title="Call: (940) 565-2333" /></a></span></strong><br style="margin: 0px;" />
		&nbsp;</p>

	<p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 20px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; margin-bottom: 8px !important;">
		Whether you want to learn how to improve your eating habits or need help with a nutrition-related health concern, seeing a registered dietitian can help. The Student Health and Wellness Center has a registered dietitian on staff to assist with:</p>

	<ul style="list-style: none; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 20px; padding-left: 2em; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;">
		<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">
			Making better food choices for overall health</li>
		<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">
			Choosing healthy options when dining on campus or at restaurant&rsquo;s</li>
		<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">
			Making budget-conscious food choices</li>
		<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">
			Improving your food preparation and cooking skills</li>
		<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">
			Gaining or losing weight</li>
		<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">
			Nutrition needs for athletes</li>
		<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">
			Diabetes</li>
		<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">
			High blood pressure</li>
		<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">
			High cholesterol or high triglycerides</li>
		<li style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">
			Gastrointestinal issues</li>
	</ul>

	<p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 20px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; margin-bottom: 8px !important;">
		This is just a small list of the services the dietitian can provide. If you have a question about whether the dietitian is able to help with another&nbsp;health concern, contact the Student Health and Wellness Center and ask to speak with the dietitian. To schedule an appointment, please call <span class="baec5a81-e4d6-4674-97f3-e9220f0136c1" style="white-space: nowrap;">940-565-2333<a href="#" style="margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;" title="Call: 940-565-2333"><img src="data:image/png;base64," style="margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;" title="Call: 940-565-2333" /></a></span>.</p>

	<p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 20px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; margin-bottom: 8px !important;">
		&nbsp;<a href="/sites/default/files/healthcenter/dietitian_ad_fall_2015.pdf" style="margin: 0px; color: rgb(68, 85, 62);" target="_blank" title="Ask a Diatitian">Click here for appointment times and prices.</a></p>

	<h4 style="margin: 0.9em 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.3em; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 1.1em;">
		Nutrition Resources for College Students</h4>

	<p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 20px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; margin-bottom: 8px !important;">
		<a href="http://www.choosemyplate.gov/" style="margin: 0px; color: rgb(68, 85, 62);" title="choosemyplate.gov">ChooseMyPlate.gov</a>&nbsp;has great resources for everyone- but especially for&nbsp;<a href="http://www.choosemyplate.gov/MyPlateOnCampus/index.html" style="margin: 0px; color: rgb(68, 85, 62);" title="MyPlateOnCampus">college students</a>! It also has&nbsp;<a href="http://www.choosemyplate.gov/MyPlateOnCampus/Recipes.html" style="margin: 0px; color: rgb(68, 85, 62);" title="MyPlateOnCampus/Recipes">recipes</a>, and other&nbsp;<a href="http://www.choosemyplate.gov/MyPlateOnCampus/Resources.html" style="margin: 0px; color: rgb(68, 85, 62);" title="MyPlateOnCampus/Resources">tips and handouts</a>&nbsp;for college students.</p>

	<p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 20px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; margin-bottom: 8px !important;">
		Also check out the Student Health and Wellness Center&nbsp;<a href="https://www.facebook.com/untSHWC?ref=hl" style="margin: 0px; color: rgb(68, 85, 62);" title="facebook.com/untSHWC">Facebook page</a>&nbsp;from time to time as the dietitian will post healthy nutrition tips and you can find weekly information about nutrition related programs and all our other health education programs and events.</p>

	<table class="sticky-enabled sticky-table" id="attachments" style="margin: 0px 0px 25px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 20px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">

				<th style="margin: 0px; padding: 7px; border: 1px solid rgb(0, 119, 0); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, &quot;Bitstream Vera Sans&quot;, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(0, 153, 0);">
